<title>USA: Nasdaq names Microsoft CFO Brown chairman.</title>
<headline>Nasdaq names Microsoft CFO Brown chairman.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-03-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Nasdaq Stock Market said on Tuesday it named Michael Brown, chief financial officer of Microsoft Corp, as chairman of the Nasdaq board of directors.</p>
<p>Brown replaces Richard DeMartini, president and chief operating officer of Dean Witter Financial Capital, whose term is expiring.</p>
<p>Brown joined Microsoft in 1989, and he joined the Nasdaq board in 1995.  </p>
<p>Nasdaq said Brown will continue in his Microsoft duties while serving as Nasdaq chairman.</p>
